# #247: an incremental trait edit that ADDS a method must regenerate the impl from the new
# trait. Before the fix, ffiGenerate (a sourceGenerator) read the stale class-dir TASTy of the
# first compile and emitted an impl missing the new method, so the second compile failed with
# "needs to be abstract". The fix reads fresh TASTy on a source change.
> compile
$ copy-file changes/TrivialBindings.scala src/main/scala/inc/TrivialBindings.scala
$ copy-file changes/trivial.c src/main/c/trivial.c
> compile
> assertImplHasIncTwo
